content.description:
Layback the edge of the chimney, then briefly enter the chimney at the third bolt. Transition onto the face past the next two bolts, to a ledge. Finish up the cruiser top section on huge pockets.

This route was put up as a solo by Eric Chemello and called 5.1. After cleaning a few thousand pounds of loose blocks out of the chimney and off the ledge, this is now an enjoyable sport route.
content.location: Look for the obvious chimney, the bolts are on the face just to the right.

content.description:
Moderate beginning past one bolt to a ledge, followed by thin and slightly overhanging climbing for the next 5 bolts to another small ledge.  The angle eases up for rest of the route, but the holds don't get much bigger.  Pull a small roof to finish.

This is an old r.b. route that was recently retrobolted with permission.  The sixth bolt is a bit right of the rest of the bolt line to avoid some hollow rock, may want to use a long draw on it.
content.location: Furthest left route at the Poison Garden, just before the Mystery Tower.

content.description: Traverse left past 3 bolts on a ramp, make a long move left, then head up. Jugs up high to a layback flake to finish.
content.location: Left side of Poison Garden wall, after you come out of the trees. This route traverses a slab from the right past 3 bolts.

content.description: Bouldery start through bulges.  Crux up high moving through small, sharp crimps.  Interesting climbing, but last 15' is super dirty.
content.location: First route to the left of Liberty.

climbs.name: Light 'Em Up
climbs.fa: Jon Guczek, Matt Delheimer and Tom Ogden 11/20

content.description: Climb the bouldery start of Into The Light, then head left. Another fun addition to the 5.10's at Marble Caves.
content.location: Same start as Into The Light then trends up and left.

content.description: A slightly pointless variation to "Pursuit Of Happiness". Hard, bouldery start, then the difficulties ease off significantly after the third bolt.
Climb an easy slab to a very high first bolt. Wrangle your way past a funky blob feature with a good left-hand pinch and up into the crack/seam. Deceptively steep through the crux.
content.location: Middle of the wall, look for the blob.

content.description: Bouldery start past the first couple bolts, to some cruiser ground, to vertical jugs for the finish.
content.location: Just left of a junky and dirty gully.

content.description: Short and bouldery route on a face to blunt arete. Better than it looks.

Moderate face to left-ward move past the 3rd bolt. Pull a bulge at the top, again on the left.

Will broke a hold on the FA and punted, hence the name.
content.location: Third route on the approach, slightly hidden behind an oak tree.

content.description:
A moderate route for the Caves!  Surprisingly vertical and clean for the grade.

Start up an easy but dirty ramp, then pull the first crux getting onto the face. Cruise up a groove/layback flake and onto the upper wall, which is studded with intrusions of black rock. A second crux comes pulling a small bulge on big holds.

The black intrusions can be a bit friable - tread lightly.
content.location: Right side of the Poison Garden, fourth route encountered on the approach.

content.description: This linkup is a harder left finish to Birdland by merging into the finish of Flight Deck. Either way, it is all excellent climbing! Once on the ledge, head up and left with mixed gear and bolts. Very, very good!
content.location: Start Birdland, then go left at the ledge at 2/3 height.

content.description: Birdland is a fun and very unique line with a lot of really enjoyable, yet thoughtful movement. Layback a crack placing a few pieces of gear. After the first bolt, stem into the left leaning dihedral and continue past two more bolts. After the third bolt run it out on 25 feet of ledgy 5.4, place a small nut on your right and step up to clip the fourth bolt up on your right. Continue climbing rightward up fun cracks to an anchor on your right.
content.protection: 4 bolts and gear: nuts (small and large), cams .5-3", Plenty of slings and long draws.

content.description: Clip the first two bolts of Diamond In The Chuff, but continue up and slightly left. A brief crux between the 3rd and 4th bolts leads to a cruiser finish.
content.location: Immediately right of the obvious vegetated gully.

content.description:
Slightly overhanging on mostly big holds; a good warm-up for the harder offerings at the Caves.

Start up a slab, clipping the second bolt off a large flat hold.  Crux comes passing this bolt and gaining the corner/ramp system using some weird stemming and a hidden pocket.  Continue up the corner to a small ledge, bear-hug a huge block, and finish up jugs to the anchor.
content.location: Middle of the Poison Garden, where you emerge from the trees.  Look for a right-leaning ramp/dihedral down low.
